The paper deals with a problem of estimating group sizes while protecting privacy, which is a common concern in data management and analysis. The use of differential privacy suggests that the paper may fall under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DB (Databases). The geographical component of the problem suggests that it may also be relevant to cs.CY (Computational Geometry) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the proposed solution involves generating consistent estimates across different levels of a hierarchy, which may be of interest to researchers in cs.LG (Machine Learning).
